&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Consultant Anaesthetist Vacancy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking to recruit three substantive Consultant Anaesthetist to our current department of 22 whole time equivalents.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Royal Orthopaedic Hospital is located in Birmingham and is an independent foundation trust providing high quality and multidisciplinary care for patients undergoing orthopaedic, spinal (including complex spine) and oncological surgery. The Trust is a tertiary referral center for both these specialties and revision arthroplasty surgery. We recently completed Phase 1 of a planned Hospital &amp; Theatre expansion which included a state-of-the-art Ward, two Theatres and recovery area which opened in January 2020, and now we are moving ahead with Phase 2 of the planned modernisation and expansion of the Hospital which will include a further two state of the art Theatres.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications are invited from enthusiastic and highly motivated anaesthetists to join our friendly and supportive department. Currently we have 22 consultants, 7 SAS doctors, 3 Physicians Assistants in Anaesthesia &amp; 2 rotating registrars from the Birmingham school of Anaesthesia.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This advertisement is for whole time consultant role’s (10PAs). On-call commitment equates to 1:8 which involves covering theatres and critical care services (level 2 only) and attracts a 0.5PA addition to the weekly clinical job plan. This job plan will include 2.5SPA with an anticipation that the successful applicants will contribute significantly to the current commitment of successfully completing ACSA within the coming two years (Accreditation of Clinical Services in Anaesthesia via the RCoA).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Within our department are six substantive specialty doctor anaesthetists, who cover first on call duties with the registrars. There are also four physician assistants (PA(A)) working in our department. They work under the supervision of a consultant anaesthetist in line with RCOA recommendations in a ratio of 1:1 or 1:2. Twin theatre working is embedded in our rota.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Anaesthetic Department provides anaesthesia services for all orthopaedic surgical procedures being carried out in the hospital including interventional radiology. We currently also have consultants contributing to pre-assessment, HDU, acute and chronic pain and perioperative medicine. We are also in the process of developing an acute pain service to complement the critical care outreach service already in place.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;*Please note: for the full advert text, please click on &#39;Additional Information&#39; which is under the job description link*&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To find out more about us, our work and our inspiring team, please visit The Royal Orthopaedic Hospital NHS Foundation Trust hospital website.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visiting Arrangements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;: &lt;/strong&gt;Interested applicants are invited to contact the hospital on the below details to discuss the vacancies further. Currently visiting restrictions are in place due to Covid-19, however as these restrictions ease we will look to arrange site visits with interested candidates at a later date:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
